Add keyboard shortcut for back navigation.

## Details
- File: renderer/src/App.tsx

## Note
This task is now part of linked-14 (Integration task). The keyboard handler will be added as part of the full App.tsx integration. This task documents the specific requirements.

## Shortcut
- Mac: Cmd+[
- Windows/Linux: Ctrl+[

## Implementation
Add to existing keyboard handler in App.tsx useEffect (around line 147-183):

```typescript
useEffect(() => {
  const handleKeyDown = (e: KeyboardEvent) => {
    // ... existing shortcuts (Cmd+K, Cmd+O, Cmd+N)

    // Cmd+[ / Ctrl+[: Navigate back
    if ((e.metaKey || e.ctrlKey) && e.key === '[') {
      e.preventDefault();
      if (canGoBack) {
        navigateBack();
      }
    }
  };

  window.addEventListener('keydown', handleKeyDown);
  return () => window.removeEventListener('keydown', handleKeyDown);
}, [isPaletteOpen, noteState, canGoBack, navigateBack]);  // Add canGoBack, navigateBack to deps
```

## Behavior
- Only triggers if canGoBack is true
- Does nothing silently if history is empty
- Prevents default browser behavior (some browsers use [ for other shortcuts)
- Works alongside existing ⌘K, ⌘O, ⌘N shortcuts

## Accessibility Notes
- Back button tooltip should mention ⌘[ (handled in linked-12)
- Consistent with browser back shortcut on Mac

## Test Scenarios
1. With history: Press Cmd+[ → navigates back
2. Without history: Press Cmd+[ → nothing happens (no error)
3. Works on both Mac (Cmd) and Windows (Ctrl)

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Cmd+[ triggers navigateBack on Mac
- [ ] Ctrl+[ triggers navigateBack on Windows/Linux
- [ ] Does nothing when no history (canGoBack false)
- [ ] Prevents default browser behavior
- [ ] No errors logged when history empty
- [ ] Integrated with existing keyboard handlers
- [ ] useEffect deps array includes canGoBack and navigateBack

