Update the metadata extraction in engine-core to recognize and extract wiki-link nodes.

## Details
- File: packages/engine-core/src/metadata.ts

## Changes to extractLinks()
Add handling for wiki-link nodes in the traverseNodes callback (around line 93-116):

```typescript
// Recursively traverse nodes to find links
traverseNodes(content.root.children, (node) => {
  // Standard link nodes with note references
  if (node.type === 'link' && typeof node.url === 'string') {
    const noteId = extractNoteIdFromUrl(node.url);
    if (noteId) {
      links.add(noteId);
    }
  }

  // Custom entity reference nodes
  if (
    node.type === 'entity-reference' &&
    node.entityType === 'note' &&
    typeof node.id === 'string'
  ) {
    links.add(node.id);
  }

  // Custom note reference nodes
  if (node.type === 'note-reference' && typeof node.noteId === 'string') {
    links.add(node.noteId);
  }

  // Wiki-link nodes (NEW)
  if (node.type === 'wiki-link' && typeof node.targetId === 'string') {
    links.add(node.targetId);
  }
});
```

## Why this matters
- Ensures wiki-links are indexed in the graph engine
- Enables backlinks queries to find wiki-links  
- Makes wiki-links part of the knowledge graph
- Existing "Show Backlinks" command will find wiki-links

## Important Notes
- Only extract targetId if it's a non-null string
- Unresolved links (targetId === null) should NOT be added to links
- The node.type will be 'wiki-link' exactly as defined in WikiLinkNode.getType()

## Tests to add in metadata.test.ts
```typescript
describe('extractLinks', () => {
  it('extracts wiki-link nodes with resolved targetId', () => {
    const content = {
      root: {
        children: [{
          type: 'paragraph',
          children: [{
            type: 'wiki-link',
            noteTitle: 'Meeting Notes',
            displayText: 'Meeting Notes',
            targetId: 'note-123'
          }]
        }]
      }
    };
    expect(extractLinks(content)).toEqual(['note-123']);
  });

  it('ignores wiki-link nodes with null targetId', () => {
    const content = {
      root: {
        children: [{
          type: 'paragraph', 
