Add IPC handler to find a note by its title for link resolution.

## Details
- Files: 
  - apps/desktop/electron/main/src/main.ts (handler)
  - apps/desktop/electron/preload/src/preload.ts (API)

## IPC Channel: notes:findByTitle

### Input
```typescript
title: string
```

### Output  
```typescript
Note | null
```

### Resolution Logic
1. Exact match: Find note where metadata.title === title
2. Case-insensitive match: Find note where metadata.title.toLowerCase() === title.toLowerCase()
3. Multiple matches: Return most recently updated (highest updatedAt)
4. No match: Return null

## Main process handler
```typescript
// Add to main.ts after existing notes handlers
ipcMain.handle('notes:findByTitle', async (_event, title: string) => {
  if (!vault) {
    throw new Error('Vault not initialized');
  }
  const notes = vault.list();

  // Exact match first
  let match = notes.find(n => n.metadata.title === title);

  // Case-insensitive fallback
  if (!match) {
    const lowerTitle = title.toLowerCase();
    const matches = notes.filter(n => 
      n.metadata.title?.toLowerCase() === lowerTitle
    );
    // Most recently updated wins
    match = matches.sort((a, b) => b.updatedAt - a.updatedAt)[0];
  }

  return match ?? null;
});
```

## Preload API
```typescript
notes: {
  // ... existing methods (list, read, create, save, delete)
  findByTitle: (title: string): Promise<Note | null> =>
    ipcRenderer.invoke('notes:findByTitle', title),
}
```

## Important Notes
- Uses `vault.list()` (synchronous) not `storage.list()` - see main.ts:109
- vault is of type FileSystemVault
- Note type from @scribe/shared

